**Three-Step Triage Process**

+----------------------+----------------------+-----------------------+
| **Step 1 --- Assess  | **Step 2 --- Check   | **Step 3 --- Decide   |
| Exploitability in    | Fix Availability**   | and Document**        |
| Your Context**       |                      |                       |
+----------------------+----------------------+-----------------------+
| **Read the CVSS      | **Check these        | **Every vulnerability |
| vector --- do not    | sources in order:**  | decision must have a  |
| rely on the score    |                      | named owner and a     |
| alone.**             | 1.  pip-audit -r     | written rationale:**  |
|                      |     requirements.txt |                       |
| -   Is AV:N? Is your |     --- lists fix    | -   Patch: record the |
|     component        |     versions         |     version patched   |
|                      |                      |     to, the date, and |
|  internet-reachable? | 2.  PyPI changelog   |     the PR/ticket     |
|                      |     for the package  |     reference.        |
| -   Is PR:N? Does    |     --- \"Security\" |                       |
|     exploitation     |     or \"CVE\"       | -   Mitigate:         |
|     require no       |     entries          |     describe the      |
|     authentication?  |                      |     compensating      |
|                      | 3.  NVD entry:       |     control, its      |
| -   Is AC:L? Are     |                      |     effectiveness,    |
|     conditions       |  nvd.nist.gov/vuln/d |     and when it will  |
|     reliably         | etail/CVE-XXXX-XXXXX |     be removed.       |
|     achievable?      |                      |                       |
|                      | 4.  CISA KEV         | -   Accept: state why |
| -   Does the         |     catalogue:       |     the risk is       |
|     vulnerable code  |     known-explo      |     acceptable in     |
|     path actually    | ited-vulnerabilities |     this context, who |
|     execute in your  |     --- if listed,   |     approved it, and  |
|     app?             |     treat as         |     when the decision |
|                      |     CRITICAL         |     will be reviewed. |
| *A CVSS 9.0 with     |     regardless of    |                       |
| AV:L (local access   |     score            | **\"We know about     |
| required) may be     |                      | it\" is not risk      |
| less urgent than a   | *If no fix exists:   | acceptance.** *Risk   |
| CVSS 7.5 with AV:N   | document the         | acceptance requires   |
| in a specific        | vulnerability,       | an explicit decision  |
| deployment. Context  | implement a          | by a named person     |
| always overrides the | compensating control | with authority to     |
